    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Compound Governor Bravo, which is the reference we got our inspiration from [doesn't agree](https://github.com/compound-finance/compound-protocol/blob/master/contracts/Governance/GovernorBravoDelegate.sol#L214).\r\n\r\nChanging that would make use inconsistent with Compound, and would make it more difficult for services like withTally.com to understand what is happening.\r\n\r\nYour proposed change (from the PR) would change the behavior if:\r\n- the quorum is 0\r\n- there are 0 for votes\r\n- there are 0 against votes\r\n\r\nUnder those circumstances, the current code makes the proposal defeated, your code would make it successful.\r\n\r\nI understand this could be debated (and devs are free to change that by overriding the `_voteSucceeded` function) ... but I do believe it is correct to mark that as a failure. One of the arguments is that this situation could happen in the case of large DOS that prevent anyone from voting. In that case, I wouldn't want the proposal to go through.",
